do, FL from January 5 - 12! |date=June 29, 2019 |accessdate=June 29, 2019}}</ref>|| DoubleTree Hilton, [[Orlando, Florida]]|| style=\"text-align: right;\" | $3,164,002<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/agdq2020|title=Awesome Games Done Quick 2020 -- Index|website=gamesdonequick.com|access-date=2020-01-15}}</ref>|| Current donation record set at a GDQ event.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2020/01/11/awesome-games-done-quick-2020-raises-over-3-1-million-for-the-prevent-cancer-foundation/ |title=Awesome Games Done Quick 2020 raises over $3.1 million for the Prevent Cancer Foundation |date=11 January 2020 |first=Mike |last=Minotti |work=[[VentureBeat]] |accessdate=12 January 2020}}</ref> Moved to Orlando, Florida to celebrate their 10th anniversary.\n|}\n\n=== Summer Games Done Quick (SGDQ) ===\nIntroduced in 2011 as a companion to AGDQ, this marathon is usually held in late June or early July and raises money for Doctors Without Borders.\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Dates !! Venue !! Charity !! Amount raised !! Notes\n|-\n| {{nowrap|August 4\u20136, 2011}} || rowspan=\"2\"| A participant's residence in [[West Bountiful, Utah]] || rowspan=\"2\"| Organisation for Autism Research<ref>{{Cite web|title = The OARacle|url = http://www.researchautism.org/resources/newsletters/2011/September_2011.asp#three|website = researchautism.org|accessdate = July 10, 2016|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304055828/http://www.researchautism.org/resources/newsletters/2011/September_2011.asp#three|archivedate = March 4, 2016}}</ref> ||style=\"text-align: right;\"| $21,397<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/sgdq2011|title=Summer Games Done Quick 2011 Donation Tracker|last=|first=|date=|website=gamesdonequick.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=January 7, 2016}}</ref>||\n|-\n| {{nowrap|May 24\u201328, 2012}} ||style=\"text-align: right;\"| $46,279<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/sgdq2012|title=Summer Games Done Quick 2012 Donation Tracker|last=|first=|date=|website=gamesdonequick.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=January 7, 2016}}</ref>||\n|-\n| {{nowrap|July 25\u201330, 2013}} || Sheraton Denver Tech Center, [[Greenwood Village, Colorado]] || rowspan=\"7\" | [[Doctors Without Borders]] ||style=\"text-align: right;\"| $257,181<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/sgdq2013|title=Summer Games Done Quick 2013 Donation Tracker|last=|first=|date=|website=gamesdonequick.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=January 7, 2016}}</ref>|| \n|-\n| {{nowrap|June 22\u201328, 2014}} || Crowne Plaza Denver International Airport, [[Denver, Colorado]] ||style=\"text-align: right;\"| $718,235<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/sgdq2014|title=Summer Games Done Quick 2014 Donation Tracker|last=|first=|date=|website=gamesdonequick.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=January 7, 2016}}</ref>|| $82,985 of the funds were raised through the SGDQ 2014 Bundle.<ref>{{cite web|title=Summer Games Done Quick 2014 Bundle |url=https://www.humblebundle.com/sgdq |accessdate=June 30, 2014 |url-status=unfit |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140630202935/https://www.humblebundle.com/sgdq |archivedate=June 30, 2014 }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{nowrap|July 26\u2013August 2, 2015}} || Crowne Plaza St. Paul Riverfront, [[Saint Paul, Minnesota]] ||style=\"text-align: right;\"| $1,215,601<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/sgdq2015|title=Summer Games Done Quick 2015 Donation Tracker|last=|first=|date=|website=gamesdonequick.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=January 7, 2016}}</ref>|| \n|-\n| {{nowrap|July 3\u20139, 2016}}<ref>{{cite tweet |user=GamesDoneQuick |author=Games Done Quick |number=686351145749639168 |title=On the #AGDQ2016 finale, we announced our dates and location for #SGDQ2016! July 3-9th, in downtown Minneapolis, MN! |date=January 10, 2016 |accessdate=January 10, 2016}}</ref> || Hilton Minneapolis Downtown, [[Minneapolis, Minnesota]] ||style=\"text-align: right;\"| $1,294,139<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/sgdq2016|title=Summer Games Done Quick 2016 Donation Tracker|last=|first=|date=|website=gamesdonequick.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=July 12, 2016}}</ref>|| First SGDQ to raise more than the AGDQ of the same year.\n|-\n| {{nowrap|July 2\u20139, 2017}}<ref>{{cite tweet |user=GamesDoneQuick |author=Games Done Quick |number=821088462006845440 |title=AGDQ 2017 was amazing, and we already can't wait for #SGDQ2017! It will be from July 2nd to the 9th at Minneapolis, Minnesota! |date=January 16, 2017 |accessdate=January 16, 2017}}</ref> || Minneapolis Marriott City Center, Minneapolis, Minnesota ||style=\"text-align: right;\"| $1,792,342<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/sgdq2017|title=Summer Games Done Quick 2017 Donation Tracker|last=|first=|date=|website=gamesdonequick.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=July 9, 2017}}</ref>|| \n|-\n| {{nowrap|June 24\u2013July 1, 2018}}<ref>{{cite tweet |user=GamesDoneQuick |author=Games Done Quick |number=952482907020505088 |title=What an awesome video from @TheBesteban, and the SGDQ 2018 dates are June 24 - July 1!!  We hope to see you there!  #AGDQ2018 |date=January 14, 2018 |accessdate=January 14, 2018}}</ref> || rowspan=\"2\" | DoubleTree Hilton, [[Bloomington, Minnesota]] || style=\"text-align: right;\" | $2,168,913<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/sgdq2018|title=Summer Games Done Quick 2018|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=14 January 2019}}</ref>||\n|-\n| {{nowrap|June 23\u201330, 2019}}<ref>{{cite tweet |user=GamesDoneQuick |author=Games Done Quick |number=1084333398510968832 |title=That's a wrap for #AGDQ2019 thank you everyone for supporting the event! We'll see you in Bloomington, MN for #SGDQ2019 from June 23 - 30! |date=January 13, 2019 |accessdate=January 13, 2019}}</ref> || style=\"text-align: right;\" | $3,039,596<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/sgdq2019|title=Summer Games Done Quick 2019|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=June 30, 2019}}</ref>|| First GDQ event to raise over $3 million, and fastest to reach $1 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nintendoenthusiast.com/2019/06/30/summer-games-done-quick-2019-raised-3-million-for-charity/ |title=Summer Games Done Quick 2019 raised $3 million for charity |date=30 June 2019 |first=Steven |last=Rollins |work=[[Nintendo Enthusiast]] |accessdate=30 June 2019}}</ref> First time an all-time donation record was set at SGDQ.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.slashgear.com/summer-games-done-quick-2019-sets-huge-donations-record-01582391/ |title=Summer Games Done Quick 2019 sets huge donations record |date=1 July 2019 |first=Eric |last=Abent|work=[[Slash Gear]] |accessdate=1 July 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{nowrap|August 16\u201323, 2020}}<ref>https://gamesdonequick.com/notice</ref> || Bloomington, Minnesota ||  ||  || Delayed from the original date due to the [[2019&ndash;20 coronavirus pandemic]].\n|}\n\n=== Games Done Quick Express (GDQx) ===\nGames Done Quick Express is an annual 4-day marathon held at [[TwitchCon]] since 2018.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Dates\n!Venue\n!Charity\n!Amount raised\n!Notes\n|-\n|{{nowrap|October 26\u201328, 2018}}<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1004030088701149184|user=GamesDoneQuick|title=GDQs are fun right? Let's have more fun then with a bonus GDQ this year! @TwitchCon and GDQ are coming together with GDQ Express, a non-stop 3-day charity speedrunning event in San Jose, CA from October 26\u201328! Runners: game submissions open 7/8! http://gamesdonequick.com/express  #GDQx|author=Games Done Quick|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=5 June 2018}}</ref>\n|[[San Jose Convention Center]]\n|10 charities{{efn|Charities at Games Done Quick Express 2018 included: [[AbleGamers]], [[American Foundation for Suicide Prevention]], [[Call of Duty#Call of Duty Endowment|Call of Duty Endowment]], [[Direct Relief]], [[Doctors Without Borders]], [[Extra Life (fundraiser)|Extra Life]], [[Make-A-Wish Foundation]], [[Save the Children]], [[St. Jude Children's Research Hospital]], and [[To Write Love on Her Arms]].<ref>[https://www.twitchcon.com/blog/2018/09/24/3-ways-to-have-fun-for-charity-at-twitchcon/ 3 ways to have fun for charity at TwitchCon]</ref>}}\n|$139,878<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/GDQX2018|title=Games Done Quick Express 2018 -- Index|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=30 October 2018}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|{{nowrap|September 27\u201329, 2019}}<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1140848616531267584|user=GamesDoneQuick|last=Games Done Quick|first=|title=We're excited to announce the return of GDQ Express at @TwitchCon in San Diego, California from September 27\u201329! Join us for a weekend full of non-stop speedrun goodness benefiting @AbleGamers! Runners: Submissions open July 7th. http://gamesdonequick.com/express\u00a0#GDQx2019|date=17 June 2019|accessdate=17 June 2019}}</ref>\n|[[San Diego Convention Center]]\n|[[The AbleGamers Foundation|AbleGamers Foundation]]\n|$152,595<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/GDQX2019|title=Games Done Quick Express 2019 -- Index|last=|first=|date=|website=gamesdonequick.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-10-26}}</ref>\n|\n|}\n\n=== Special Marathons ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|-\n! Marathon !! Dates !! Venue !! Charity !! Amount raised !! Notes\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| Japan Relief Done Quick || {{nowrap|April 7\u201310, 2011}} || Runners streamed from their residences || Doctors Without Borders || $25,800<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/jrdq|title=Japan Relief Done Quick \u2013 Donation total: $25,800.33|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=14 January 2019}}</ref>|| A marathon to support victims of the [[2011 T\u014dhoku earthquake and tsunami]].\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| Speedrun Spooktacular || {{nowrap|October 26\u201329, 2012}} || Runners streamed from their residences || Lindsey King || $9,733<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/spook|title=Speedrun Spooktacular \u2013 Donation total: $9,732.99|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=14 January 2019}}</ref>|| A marathon to help medical bills for Lindsey King, an artist for [[Speed Demos Archive]].\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| God of War Done Quick || {{nowrap|March 20, 2015}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.us.playstation.com/2015/03/16/watch-god-of-war-done-quick-live-march-20th/|title=Watch God of War Done Quick, Live March 20th|author1=Kaufman, Aaron|author2=Community Strategist|date=16 March 2015|publisher=Sony Computer Entertainment America LLC|accessdate=17 March 2015|author3=Santa Monica Studio}}</ref> || [[SCE Santa Monica Studio|Sony Santa Monica Studio]] || [[The AbleGamers Foundation|AbleGamers Foundation]] || $3,500+<ref>{{cite tweet|number=579095583689830400|user=GamesDoneQuick|title=Thanks to everyone who helped raise over $3500 for @AbleGamers and create an incredibly fun stream at @SonySantaMonica today! It was amazing|author=Games Done Quick|date=20 March 2015|accessdate=20 March 2015}}</ref> || Special event at [[SCE Santa Monica Studio|Sony Santa Monica Studio]] as part of the 10 year anniversary of the [[God of War (franchise)|''God of War'' franchise]].\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| Harvey Relief Done Quick || {{nowrap|September 1\u20133, 2017}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GamesDoneQuick/status/902954616794607617|title=Harvey Relief Done Quick is official! Fri. 8PM - Sun. 8PM EDT. Game Submissions will be live (via Google Forms) within the hour. #HRDQ2017|last=Games Done Quick|first=|date=2017-08-30|website=Twitter|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>|| Runners streamed from their residences || [[Houston Food Bank]] || $229,455<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/hrdq|title=Harvey Relief Done Quick \u2013 Donation total: $229,454.94|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=14 January 2019}}</ref> || A marathon to support victims of [[Hurricane Harvey]] in Texas.\n|-\n|Classic Games Done Quick (CGDQ) 10th Anniversary\n|December 27-29, 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GamesDoneQuick/status/1196926124980228097|title=GDQ is celebrating its 10th anniversary in 2020! We're throwing it back to the first GDQ, Classic Games Done Quick, from 12/27 to 12/29. We'll be reprising the CGDQ schedule with both original runners and many new ones live on <nowiki>http://twitch.tv/gamesdonequick</nowiki>\u00a0!|last=Games Done Quick|first=|date=2019-11-19|website=Twitter|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n|Runners streamed from their residences\n|N/A\n|N/A\n|Exact recreation of the schedule of the 1st event in January 2010 to celebrate 10 years of GDQ. \n|-\n|Corona Relief Done Quick\n|April 17-19, 2020\n|Runners streamed from their residences\n|[[Direct Relief]]\n|$402,568<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/crdq|title=Corona Relief Done Quick \u2013 Donation total: $402,568.60|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|accessdate=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n|A marathon to help improve the health and lives of people affected by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GamesDoneQuick/status/1243567589890154496|title=We'd like to share some updates regarding GDQ and COVID-19|date=2020-03-27|website=Twitter|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.polygon.com/2020/4/20/21227858/games-done-quick-coronavirus-relief-fund-crdq-april-2020 | title = Games Done Quick raises $400K for coronavirus relief fund | first = Nicole | last = Carpenter | date = April 20, 2020 | accessdate = April 20, 2020 | work = [[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] }}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{portal|Video games}}\n*{{Official website|gamesdonequick.com}}\n*[https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/runs/ All Runs At a GDQ]\n\n{{Speedrunning}}\n\n[[Category:Charity events in the United States]]\n[[Category:Speedrunning]]\n[[Category:Video game events]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Bi-annual video game speedrun charity marathon}}\n{{Redirect|GDQ|the airport|Gondar Airport|the language|Mehri language}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox convention\n| name = Games Done Quick\n| image = Games Done Quick logo 2018.png\n| status = Active\n| genre = Video game [[speedrun]]s<br/>[[Video games and charity]]\n| venue = Various\n| location = Various\n| country = [[United States]]\n| first = {{Start date and years ago|2010|01|01}}\n| last = {{Start date and years ago|2020|02|29}}\n| next = {{Start date and years ago|2020|08|16}}\n| organizer = Games Done Quick, LLC\n| founder_name = Mike Uyama<ref name=\"Founder\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/how-games-done-quick-raises-millions-charity-1172902 |title=How an Event Dedicated to Playing Video Games as Fast as Possible Raises Millions For Charity |date=4 January 2019 |first=Patrick |last=Shanley |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=13 January 2019}}</ref>\n| website = {{URL|gamesdonequick.com}}\n}}\n'''Games Done Quick''' is a semiannual [[video game]] [[speedrun]] charity marathon held in the [[United States]], originally organized by the [[Speed Demos Archive]] and Speedruns Live communities. Since 2015, it has been handled by Games Done Quick, LLC.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/privacy|publisher=Games Done Quick, LLC|title=Privacy Policy|date=6 August 2015}}</ref> Held since 2010, the events have raised money for several charities.\n\nThe two flagship events held by Games Done Quick are Awesome Games Done Quick (AGDQ), held in early January every year, which raises money for the [[Prevent Cancer Foundation]], and Summer Games Done Quick (SGDQ), usually held in late June or early July every year, which raises money for [[Doctors Without Borders]]. Both events last for 7 days. In addition to these events, GDQ hosts several other broadcasts throughout the year including smaller marathons supporting different charities, one-off events for special occasions, and regular GDQ Hotfix programming throughout the year.\n\nThe events are broadcast live on [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]]. Viewers are encouraged to donate for incentives during the stream such as selecting the file name or main character's name in a run, having the runners attempt more difficult challenges, and entering raffles for the chance of winning prizes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://associationsnow.com/2015/01/gaming-gurus-reinvented-telethons-web/|publisher=Association Now|title=How Gaming Gurus Reinvented Telethons for the Web|last=Smith|first=Ernie|date=January 13, 2015}}</ref> Over $25.7 million has been raised across 25 marathons.<ref name=\"Total\">{{cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/|title=All Events \u2013 Donation total: $25,742,182.26|last=|first=|date=30 June 2020|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick, LLC|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=27 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Format==\nSpeedrunners take turns demonstrating their prowess at beating various video games in the quickest possible time, done in front of an audience as well as a [[Live streaming|livestream]] through [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://kotaku.com/watch-the-first-day-of-the-weeklong-awesome-games-done-1790948260|title=Watch The Final Days Of The Weeklong Awesome Games Done Quick Charity Marathon|last=Gach|first=Ethan|newspaper=Kotaku|language=en-US|access-date=January 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2017/01/prepare-your-switch-tab-shortcut-at-work-awesome-games-done-quick-is-back/|title=Awesome Games Done Quick is indeed awesome, will ruin productivity all week|newspaper=Ars Technica|access-date=January 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2017/01/09/awesome-games-done-quick-2017-started/|title=Awesome Games Done Quick speedruns another week|last=O'Connor|first=Alice|date=January 9, 2017|website=Rock, Paper, Shotgun|language=en-US|access-date=January 14, 2017}}</ref> Sometimes these runs may be executed in an unusual or specific way, such as fully completing every level, completing a game blindfolded,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2016/7/5/12098530/speedrunner-castlevania-symphony-of-the-night-romscout-blindfolded-games-done-quick|title=Watch a speedrunner complete Castlevania: Symphony of the Night blindfolded|last=Biery|first=Thomas|date=July 5, 2016|website=Polygon|access-date=January 14, 2017}}</ref> or featuring multiple runners racing against one another to complete a game first.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/01/13/11-amazing-speedruns-from-awesome-games-done-quick-2016|title=11 Amazing Speedruns from Awesome Games Done Quick 2016|last=Otero|first=Jose|date=January 12, 2016|website=IGN|language=en-US|access-date=January 14, 2017}}</ref> Video games run in Games Done Quick events include both [[retrogaming|retro]] and modern titles. The runs typically feature commentary from the runner(s) or experienced commentators, as well as donation messages read by an announcer.\n\nMost of the popular runs feature video game glitches<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2016/7/9/12135296/summer-games-done-quick-2016-roundup-sgdq-2016|title=Summer Games Done Quick 2016 roundup: The biggest surprises of the week|last=Biery|first=Thomas|date=July 9, 2016|website=Polygon|access-date=January 14, 2017}}</ref> and discussion between the runner and the commentators, most frequently describing techniques or using observational humor and banter.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2015/07/what-to-watch-during-the-summer-games-done-quick-speedrun-marathon/|title=What to watch during the Summer Games Done Quick speedrun marathon|newspaper=Ars Technica|access-date=January 14, 2017}}</ref> Humor and banter is especially used for non-interactive or repetitive sequences that don't require the runner to use much or any skill. Donations from viewers may feature humorous comments that contain inside jokes among the speedrunning community, as well as more personal acknowledgements concerning the charity donated to. Because of the live broadcast and wider audience, runners and commentators are encouraged to refrain from using strong profanity and offensive behavior.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/rules|title=Games Done Quick|website=gamesdonequick.com|access-date=January 14, 2017}}</ref>\n\nWhen donating, donors have the option to put their money towards a particular incentive. These incentives can be in the form of bonus speedruns, showcases of additional tricks or glitches or an in-game decision such as naming the player character.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Games Done Quick logo.PNG|thumb|left|150px|Games Done Quick's former logo, used until 2018]]\nWriter and speedrunner Eric Koziel identifies two important precursors to Games Done Quick: the \"Desert Bus for Hope\" donation drive organized by [[LoadingReadyRun]] in November 2007, and a series of charity speedrun marathons held by The Speed Gamers starting in March 2008.<ref name=\"Koziel\">{{cite web|url=https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0014/1962/files/SpeedrunScience-010518_4e78a515-1852-4daf-ad5f-3f870cd569a8.pdf |date=January 5, 2018 |title=Speedrun Science: A Long Guide to Short Playthroughs |author=Koziel, Eric |publisher=Fangamer}}</ref>\n\nUsers of the site Speed Demos Archive decided to hold a charity marathon in January 2010,<ref name=\"MyUser_Wired.com_January_9_2016c\">{{cite web |url=https://www.wired.com/2014/01/awesome-games-done-quick-2014/ |title=Speeding Through Classic Games to Beat Cancer |newspaper=Wired.com |date=  |author= |accessdate= January 9, 2016}}</ref> during [[MAGFest]] 8. It was themed around 8-bit and 16-bit video games and thus dubbed \"Classic Games Done Quick\" (after the 1990s speedrunning project Quake Done Quick). Internet connectivity problems at the MAGFest hotel forced SDA administrator Mike Uyama to relocate the event to his mother's residence, but it raised over $10,000 for [[CARE (relief agency)|CARE]].<ref name=\"Koziel\"/><ref name=\"MyUser_Vice.com_January_9_2016c\">{{cite web |url=https://www.vice.com/en_uk/read/summer-games-done-quick-is-this-weekend-watch-and-be-wowed-333 |title=Summer Games Done Quick Starts This Weekend: Watch and Be Wowed |newspaper=Vice.com |date=  |author= |accessdate= January 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\nFollowing that initial success, the first Awesome Games Done Quick marathon was held in January 2011, expanding from two days to five days, incorporating newer games such as ''[[Halo: Combat Evolved|Halo]]'' and ''[[Portal (video game)|Portal]]'', and raising more than $50,000 for the Prevent Cancer Foundation.<ref name=\"MyUser_Kevinbondelli.com_January_9_2016c\">{{cite web |url=http://www.kevinbondelli.com/2013/01/11/awesome-games-done-quick-has-already-raised-250k-for-prevent-cancer-foundation/#.VpFuvX2LTnA |title=Awesome Games Done Quick Has Already Raised $250K for Prevent Cancer Foundation |newspaper=Kevinbondelli.com |date= |author= |accessdate=January 9, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160324194256/http://www.kevinbondelli.com/2013/01/11/awesome-games-done-quick-has-already-raised-250k-for-prevent-cancer-foundation/#.VpFuvX2LTnA |archive-date=March 24, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The first Summer Games Done Quick was held in August 2011, raising $20,000 for the Organisation for Autism Research.<ref name=\"MyUser_Researchautism.org_January_9_2016c\">{{cite web |url=http://www.researchautism.org/resources/newsletters/2011/September_2011.asp |title=September_2011 |newspaper=Researchautism.org |accessdate=January 9, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304055828/http://www.researchautism.org/resources/newsletters/2011/September_2011.asp |archivedate=March 4, 2016 }}</ref><ref name=\"MyUser_Https:_January_9_2016c\">{{cite web |url=https://netguide.co.nz/story/gamers-speed-run-for-charity/ |title=NetGuide NZ - Gamers speed-run for charity |newspaper=Https |date=  |author= |accessdate= January 9, 2016}}</ref> Since then, both Awesome Games Done Quick and Summer Games Done Quick have recurred annually, raising larger amounts each year.\n\nA one-off additional marathon was held in March 2011 to support victims of the [[2011 T\u014dhoku earthquake and tsunami|earthquake and tsunami in Japan]]; Japan Relief Done Quick raised over $25,000. In addition, a one-off promotional event was held on March 20, 2015 to celebrate the 10th anniversary of the [[God of War (franchise)|''God of War'' franchise]]. Over the course of five hours, God of War Done Quick ended up raising $3,500 for [[The AbleGamers Foundation]].\n\nIn 2020, Games Done Quick expelled a speedrunner for violating social media policies after the runner made remarks on Twitter that supported [[antifeminism]] and the far-right Spanish party [[Vox (political party)|Vox]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Games Done Quick let proud anti-feminist speedrunner stream to over 100,000 viewers |url=https://www.dailydot.com/parsec/gdq-anti-feminist-speedrunner/ |accessdate=14 January 2020 |work=The Daily Dot |date=8 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Malmgren |first1=Evan |title=GDQ Suspends Speedrunner With 'Feminazism' In Twitter Profile, Raising Lots Of Questions |url=https://kotaku.com/gdq-suspends-speedrunner-with-feminazism-in-twitter-pro-1840979327 |accessdate=14 January 2020 |work=Kotaku |language=en-us}}</ref>\n\nDuring the start of Frost Fatales 2020, they announced their new GDQ Studio to produce in-person live events outside of the normal marathons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/VanCamp/status/1231788865188454400|title=We built a dang studio. A huge team has poured an enormous amount into making this show possible, and the crew on-site is doing a wonderful job. Check it out if you have a minute <nowiki>https://twitter.com/GamesDoneQuick/status/1231630987001548805</nowiki>\u00a0\u2026|last=Camp|first=Alex Van|date=2020-02-23|website=Twitter|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\n==List of marathons==\n=== Awesome Games Done Quick (AGDQ) ===\nOriginally called Classic Games Done Quick (CGDQ), this annual marathon is held every year in early January raising money for the Prevent Cancer Foundation.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Dates !! Venue !! Charity !! Amount raised !! Notes\n|-\n|{{nowrap|January 1\u20133, 2010}}||''(planned)'' Hilton Alexandria Mark Center, [[Alexandria, Virginia]] (during [[MAGFest|MAGFest 8]]; one speedrun was completed before venue was changed)\n''(actual)'' private residence\n|[[CARE (relief agency)|CARE]]|| style=\"text-align: right;\" | $10,532<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/cgdq|title=Classic Games Done Quick \u2013 Donation total: $10,531.64|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=30 October 2018}}</ref>|| \n|-\n|{{nowrap|January 6\u201311, 2011}}|| rowspan=\"3\" | National [[4-H]] Youth Conference Center, [[Chevy Chase, Maryland]]|| rowspan=\"10\" |[[Prevent Cancer Foundation]]|| style=\"text-align: right;\" | $52,520<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/agdq2011|title=Awesome Games Done Quick 2011 \u2013 Donation total: $52,519.83|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=30 October 2018}}</ref>||First event to be called Awesome Games Done Quick\n|-\n|{{nowrap|January 4\u20139, 2012}}|| style=\"text-align: right;\" | $149,045<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/agdq2012|title=Awesome Games Done Quick 2012 \u2013 Donation total: $149,044.99|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=30 October 2018}}</ref>|| \n|-\n|{{nowrap|January 6\u201312, 2013}}|| style=\"text-align: right;\" | $448,425<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/agdq2013|title=Awesome Games Done Quick 2013 \u2013 Donation total: $448,425.27|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=30 October 2018}}</ref>||\n|-\n|{{nowrap|January 5\u201311, 2014}}|| Crowne Plaza Dulles, [[Herndon, Virginia]]|| style=\"text-align: right;\" | $1,031,667<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/agdq2014|title=Awesome Games Done Quick 2014 \u2013 Donation total: $1,031,665.50|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=30 October 2018}}</ref>|| First GDQ event to raise over $1 million.\n|-\n|{{nowrap|January 4\u201310, 2015}}|| rowspan=\"4\" | Hilton Washington Dulles, Herndon, Virginia || style=\"text-align: right;\" | $1,576,085<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gamesdonequick.com/tracker/event/agdq2015|title=Awesome Games Done Quick 2015 \u2013 Donation total: $1,576,085.00|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Games Done Quick|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=30 October 2018}}</ref>||\n|-\n|{{nowrap|January 3\u20