y]])</small>\n|rowspan=2|''[[Tia & Tamera]]''\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|Choice Reality TV Star: Female<br>(shared with Tia Mowry)\n|{{Nom}}\n|}\n\n===Young Artist Award===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Award\n!Performance\n!Result\n|-\n|1995\n|Best Youth Comedienne in a TV Show<br><small>(shared with [[Tia Mowry]])</small>\n|rowspan=3|''[[Sister, Sister (TV series)|Sister, Sister]]''\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|1996\n|Best Performance by a Young Actress&nbsp;\u2013 TV Comedy Series<br><small>(shared with Tia Mowry)</small>\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|1997\n|Best Performance in a TV Comedy&nbsp;\u2013 Leading Young Actress<br><small>(shared with Tia Mowry)</small>\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|2001\n|Best Performance in a TV Movie (Comedy)&nbsp;\u2013 Leading Young Actress<br><small>(shared with Tia Mowry)</small>\n|''[[Seventeen Again]]''\n|{{Nom}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://tiaandtameraofficial.com/ Official Website]\n*{{IMDb name|5255}}\n\n{{Daytime Emmy Award Outstanding Entertainment Talk Show Host}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mowry, Tamera}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:African-American actresses]]\n[[Category:African-American Christians]]\n[[Category:American child actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American people of Bahamian descent]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Identical twin actresses]]\n[[Category:Pepperdine University alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Military brats]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:People from Gelnhausen]]\n[[Category:Twin people from the United States]]\n[[Category:Voices (group) members]]\n[[Category:African-American television talk show hosts]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name                  = Tamera Mowry\n|image=\n|image_size             =\n|caption                =\n| birth_name            = Tamera Darvette Mowry\n| birth_date            = {{Birth date and age|1978|7|6|mf=y}}\n| birth_place           = [[Gelnhausen]], [[West Germany]]\n| death_date            =\n| death_place           =\n| alma_mater            = [[Pepperdine University]]\n| occupation            = Actress, TV host\n| television  = {{flatlist|\n*''[[Sister, Sister (TV series)|Sister, Sister]]''<br /> ''[[Tia & Tamera]]''<br />''[[The Real (TV series)|The Real]]''\n}}\n| spouse                = {{marriage|[[Adam Housley]]|May 15, 2011}}\n| children              = 2\n| relatives             = [[Tia Mowry-Hardrict]] {{small|(twin sister)}}<br>[[Tahj Mowry]] {{small|(brother)}}\n| website               =  {{url|http://www.tameramowry.com/}}\n| othername             =\n| years active          = 1990\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Tamera Darvette Mowry-Housley'''<ref name=\"filmref\">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/80/Tamera-Mowry.html|title=Tamera Mowry Biography (1978-)\n| publisher=FilmReference.com|accessdate=November 13, 2012| archivedate= March 3, 2016| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160303212152/http://www.filmreference.com/film/80/Tamera-Mowry.html | url-status=live}}</ref> {{IPAc-en|t|\u0259|'|m|\u025b|r|\u0259|_|'|m|\u0254\u02d0r|i}} (n\u00e9e '''Mowry'''; born July 6, 1978)<ref name=\"filmref\" /> is an American actress and TV show host. She first gained fame for her teen role as Tamera Campbell on the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]/[[The WB|WB]] [[situation comedy|sitcom]] ''[[Sister, Sister (TV series)|Sister, Sister]]'' (opposite her [[identical twin]] sister [[Tia Mowry]]).<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/ca/news/495543/tia-and-tamera-mowry-end-reality-show-run|title=Tia and Tamera Mowry End Reality Show Run|last=|first=|date=2014-01-03|website=E! News|language=en-CA|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-09-19}}</ref> She has also starred in the [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Twitches (film)|Twitches]]'' and its sequel, ''[[Twitches Too]]'', and she played Dr. Kayla Thornton on the [[medical drama]] ''[[Strong Medicine]]''.\n\nShe next starred in a reality television series following her and her twin sister's lives, titled ''[[Tia & Tamera]]'', which began airing on the [[Style Network]] in 2011 and ended in 2013 after three seasons.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/tia-and-tamera-mowry-end-reality-series-tia-tamera-after-three-seasons-201431/|title=Tia & Tamera Mowry End Reality Series After Three Seasons|date=2014-01-03|website=Us Weekly|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-19}}</ref> Mowry is one of the co-hosts of the syndicated daytime talk show, ''[[The Real (TV series)|The Real]]'', alongside [[Loni Love]], [[Adrienne Bailon]], [[Jeannie Mai]], and [[Amanda Seales]], which has aired since 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=It\u2019s Official: \u2018The Real\u2019 Talk Show Begins Four-Week Test Run July 15|url=https://www.deadline.com/2013/06/real-talk-show-july-15-premiere-test-run-fox/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=28 July 2013|date=June 12, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nTamera Darvette Mowry was born in [[Gelnhausen]] in then-[[West Germany]] on July 6, 1978 to Darlene Renee Mowry (n\u00e9e Flowers), who served in the U.S. Army and later became her children's manager, and Timothy John Mowry, who was in the U.S. Army at the time of her birth and who became a custody officer/jailer with the City of Glendale Police Department when the family moved to California.<ref name=filmref/><ref name=\"Italian\">{{cite web |url= http://www.geocities.com/tiaandtameramowryonline/pw_interview1994.html |type= interviews |accessdate= January 4, 2010 |work= [[People (magazine)|People]] |date= May 9, 1994 |volume=4 |issue=17 |page=175 |title= Winsome twinsome: Tia and Tamera Mowry are 'Sister, Sister's sibling schemers | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080801000033/http://www.geocities.com/tiaandtameramowryonline/pw_interview1994.html |archivedate= August 1, 2008 }}</ref><ref name=\"info\">\"[http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1355/is_13_95/ai_54724890 Tia, Tamera And Tahj Mowry Keep Laughter In The Family With Hit TV Shows 'Sister, Sister' And 'Smart Guy']\". Findarticles.com (1999-03-01). Retrieved on 2012-07-06.</ref> Tamera Mowry is the older twin by two minutes. Tamera was born at 4:30pm, followed by Tia at 4:32pm. She also has two younger brothers named [[Tahj Mowry]], an actor, and Tavior Mowry, who played college football for [[University of California, Davis]].\n\nHer father has English and Irish ancestry, and her mother is of Afro-Bahamian descent.<ref>On her talk show, ''[[The Real]]'', Tamera discovered that her [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e2JxoDyexiQ Mother's descendants came from Ghana]. During an appearance on ''[[The Wendy Williams Show]]'' in 2010, it was stated that for years, the Mowrys had believed that they had Italian ancestry on their father's side; however, after researching their family tree on [[Ancestry.com]], they discovered that their father has Irish ancestry.</ref> Mowry's parents met in [[high school]], in [[Miami, Florida]], both joining the [[United States Army|U.S. Army]], and both eventually reaching the rank of sergeant.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20080109235123/http://www.christianitytoday.com/tc/2005/002/14.42.html Double Devotion&nbsp;\u2013 Today's Christian]. Web.archive.org (2008-01-09). Retrieved on 2012-07-06.</ref> Mowry has described her family as being both \"close-knit\" and \"deeply religious\",<ref name=\"info\"/> and the sisters became [[Born again (Christianity)|born-again Christians]] when they were eight years old.<ref>[http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1077/is_n1_v54/ai_21270369 TV's tantalizing twins: Tia and Tamera Mowry share 'Sister Sister' sitcom, schoolwork and singing]. Findarticles.com. Retrieved on 2012-07-06.</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n===Television===\nMowry and her twin sister, [[Tia Mowry|Tia]], co-starred in the 2005 [[Disney Channel]] film ''[[Twitches (film)|Twitches]]''.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Dempsey|first=John|date=2007-10-15|title=Audiences \u2018Twitch\u2019 for Disney|url=https://variety.com/2007/scene/markets-festivals/audiences-twitch-for-disney-1117974089/|journal=Variety}}</ref> In 2013, Mowry became a co-host of syndicated daytime talk show, ''[[The Real (talk show)|The Real]]'', alongside [[Adrienne Bailon]], [[Loni Love]], [[Jeannie Mai]], and [[Amanda Seales]]. The series premiered on July 15.<ref>{{cite web|title=It\u2019s Official: \u2018The Real\u2019 Talk Show Begins Four-Week Test Run July 15|url=https://www.deadline.com/2013/06/real-talk-show-july-15-premiere-test-run-fox/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=28 July 2013|date=June 12, 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Other ventures===\nTo kick off motherhood, Mowry and her twin sister, Tia, planned on starting a project, Need Brand.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://naturalchildworld.com/tia-tamera-mowry-actors-and-founders-need-brand/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141206045901/http://naturalchildworld.com/tia-tamera-mowry-actors-and-founders-need-brand/|url-status=dead|archive-date=2014-12-06|title=Tia & Tamera Mowry Actors and Founders of NEED Brand {{!}} Natural Child World|website=naturalchildworld.com|access-date=2016-06-08}}</ref> Milky! and Stretchy! are two of the products that can cater to motherhood. Milky! is a 2.5 oz. bottle with all organic ingredients that can help mothers produce milk. Stretchy! is a stretch mark cream for post-operation scars.\n\nAnother sibling project includes a two-book series called ''Twintuition: Double Vision'' and ''Twintuition: Double Trouble''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.harpercollins.com/9780062372864/twintuition-double-vision|title=Twintuition: Double Vision - Tia Mowry, Tamera Mowry - Hardcover|last=Archipelago|first=World|website=HarperCollins US|access-date=2016-06-08}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn July 2013, Mowry-Housley revealed that she did not lose her [[virginity]] until she was 29 due to her being a devout Christian. She elaborated that she felt guilty after she had sex, and afterward committed to remaining [[celibacy|celibate]] until marriage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/07/19/tamera-mowry-housley-virginity_n_3622463.html|title=Tamera Mowry-Housley Talks About Losing Her Virginity At 29, Staying Celibate Until Her Wedding|website=[[Huffington Post]]|publisher=[[Huffington Post Media Group]]|location=New York City|date=July 19, 2013|accessdate=March 13, 2017}}</ref> She married [[Fox News]] correspondent [[Adam Housley]],<ref>{{cite magazine|first1= Ulrica|last1=Wihlborg|first2=Sara|last2=Hammel|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20459457,00.html|title=Tamera's engagement to marry Housley|magazine=[[people (magazine)|People]]|publisher=[[Meredith Corporation]]|location=New York City|date=January 20, 2011|accessdate=July 6, 2012}}</ref> after dating for almost six years, on May 15, 2011 in California's [[Napa County, California|Napa Valley]]. The couple welcomed their first child, a son, Aden John Tanner Housley, on November 12, 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/blogs/entertainment/2012/11/tamera-mowry-housley-adam-housley-welcome-baby|title=Tamera Mowry-Housley, Adam Housley Welcome Baby|website=[[American Broadcasting Corporation]]|date=November 14, 2012|accessdate=December 3, 2012}}</ref> and their second child, daughter Ariah Talea Housley, on July 1, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tamera Mowry Gives Birth! Actress Welcomes Baby No. 2 With Adam Housley |url= http://www.eonline.com/news/671212/tamera-mowry-gives-birth-actress-welcomes-baby-no-2-with-adam-housley |website=[[E! Online]]|publisher=[[E!]] |location=Los Angeles, California |date=July 1, 2015 |accessdate= February 16, 2018}}</ref>\nAs well as fans will have a chance to get a glimpse into Tamera's family life through her new [[YouTube]] series, \u201cThe Housley Life,\u201d<ref>{{YouTube user|https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC9Lnm2KU5l-oaLT5evEPn5g|The Housley Life}}</ref> which follows the family on their daily adventures, special occasions and the unpredictability that comes with having kids.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.amomama.com/167162-see-tamera-mowrys-daughter-ariahs-bright.html|title=\tSee Tamera Mowry's Daughter Ariah's Bright Smile during a Car Ride|website=AmoMama|accessdate=August 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\nShe had a [[Shih Tzu]] named Milano.<ref>{{cite news |title=Inside Sister, Sister Star Tamera Mowry's Wedding |url= http://people.com/celebrity/inside-sister-sister-star-tamera-mowrys-wedding/flower-girl|magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]]|publisher=[[Meredith Corporation]]|location=New York City|accessdate=February 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\nMowry-Housley's niece, Alaina Housley (born in 2000) was among the victims of the [[Thousand Oaks shooting|shooting]] at the Borderline Bar and Grill in [[Thousand Oaks, California]], on November 7, 2018.<ref>{{cite news|first=Alicia|last=Adejobi|title=Tamera Mowry confirms her niece Alaina Housley died in the California bar shooting |url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/11/08/tamera-mowry-confirmed-her-niece-alaina-housley-died-in-the-california-bar-shooting-8120462/|newspaper=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|publisher=[[DMG Media]]|location=London, England|date=November 8, 2018|accessdate=February 16, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2002\n|''{{sortname|The|Hot Chick}}''\n|Sissy\n|\n|-\n|2012\n|''Redemption of a Dog''\n|Michelle\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1991\n|''[[Flesh 'n' Blood (TV series)|Flesh 'n' Blood]]''\n|Penelope\n|\"Beauty Is in the Eye of the Ticketholder\"\n|-\n|1992\n|''[[True Colors (TV series)|True Colors]]''\n|Lorae\n